definitions.definition: ( countable ) A member of a Germanic people who live in parts of northeast Italy .
( countable , historical ) A member of the Cimbri , especially when they are considered to have been a Germanic people and to originate from Jutland (the "Cimbrian peninsula").

main_definition: ( countable ) A member of a Germanic people who live in parts of northeast Italy .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , historical ) A member of the Cimbri , especially when they are considered to have been a Germanic people and to originate from Jutland (the "Cimbrian peninsula").

definitions.definition: The Bavarian Germanic language of these people, which is a variety of German .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) The Bavarian Germanic language of these people, which is a variety of German .
